intro: Teline candicans, commonly known as the showy teline, is a flowering plant belonging to the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its finely divided, fern-like leaves and clusters of small, white to pale yellow flowers. The plant typically grows in moist, open habitats such as meadows and woodland edges. It is native to parts of Europe and has been introduced to other regions. Teline candicans is valued for its ornamental appeal and its role in supporting pollinators.
